{
  "id": "L15",
  "title": "At the Doctor's Office",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you will learn how to talk to a doctor in the Netherlands. The Dutch word for a general practitioner is 'huisarts'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V01",
      "data": {
        "De huisarts": "The GP / doctor"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V02",
      "data": {
        "De afspraak": "The appointment"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Goedemiddag",
        "meaning": "Good afternoon"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V03",
      "data": {
        "Ik heb": "I have"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik heb een afspraak",
        "meaning": "I have an appointment"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V04",
      "data": {
        "De hoofdpijn": "The headache"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik heb hoofdpijn",
        "meaning": "I have a headache"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L15_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "hoofdpijn",
        "phonetic": "/'hoːft.pɛin/",
        "tip": "The 'oo' is a long sound, like in 'hope'. The 'ij' sounds like the 'i' in 'fine'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V05",
      "data": {
        "Drie": "Three"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V06",
      "data": {
        "De dagen": "The days"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Al drie dagen",
        "meaning": "For three days"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S01",
      "title": "Checking In",
      "setting": "You arrive at the doctor's office. You first speak to the receptionist, then the doctor calls you in.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet the receptionist",
          "chatbot_message": "Goedemiddag."
        },
        {
          "title": "State that you have an appointment",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké."
        },
        {
          "title": "Explain your main symptom",
          "chatbot_message": "Goedemiddag. Wat is het probleem?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say how long you have had the problem",
          "chatbot_message": "Hoe lang heb je al hoofdpijn?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Listen to the doctor's response",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké. Drie dagen."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V07",
      "data": {
        "De klacht": "The complaint / symptom"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V08",
      "data": {
        "Ook": "Also / too"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V09",
      "data": {
        "De koorts": "The fever"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik heb ook koorts",
        "meaning": "I also have a fever"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "When you want to add another symptom or piece of information, you can use the word 'ook' (also)."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V10",
      "data": {
        "Mijn": "My"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V11",
      "data": {
        "Het hoofd": "The head"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Mijn hoofd doet pijn",
        "meaning": "My head hurts"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V12",
      "data": {
        "Ja": "Yes"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V13",
      "data": {
        "De medicijnen": "The medicines"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V14",
      "data": {
        "Paracetamol": "Paracetamol"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S02",
      "title": "Answering Questions",
      "setting": "The conversation with the doctor continues. They are asking more questions to understand your problem.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Describe another symptom",
          "chatbot_message": "Heb je nog andere klachten?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Answer where it hurts",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké. En waar doet het pijn?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Tell the doctor what you have taken",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké, je hoofd. Heb je medicijnen genomen?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Listen to the doctor's acknowledgement",
          "chatbot_message": "Paracetamol. Goed."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V15",
      "data": {
        "Langzaam": "Slowly"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V16",
      "data": {
        "Alstublieft": "Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Kan je dat langzaam zeggen?",
        "meaning": "Can you say that slowly?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "If you don't understand, it's very useful to ask: 'Kan je dat langzaam zeggen, alstublieft?'"
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V17",
      "data": {
        "Het recept": "The prescription"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L15_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "recept",
        "phonetic": "/rəˈsɛpt/",
        "tip": "The 'c' in the middle is pronounced like an 's'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V18",
      "data": {
        "Nodig": "Necessary / needed"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Heb ik een recept nodig?",
        "meaning": "Do I need a prescription?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To make a noun negative, use 'geen'. For example, 'ik heb een recept' (I have a prescription) becomes 'ik heb geen recept' (I have no prescription)."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank je wel",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Bedankt",
        "meaning": "Thanks"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S03",
      "title": "Understanding the Advice",
      "setting": "The doctor has finished the examination and is giving you advice.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask the doctor to repeat slowly",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké. Advies: veel water drinken en veel rusten."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if you need a prescription",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja. Drink veel water. En rust veel."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the doctor",
          "chatbot_message": "Nee, je hebt geen recept nodig. Paracetamol is goed."
        },
        {
          "title": "End the conversation",
          "chatbot_message": "Graag gedaan. Beterschap!"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}